SLS 26RS-4638 ORIGINAL
2026 Regular Session
SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 208
BY SENATOR CATHEY
VETERANS. Directs the Department of Veteran Affairs to submit a report annually to the
Legislature outlining the length of time between discharge of military and a claim for
services.
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To direct the Louisiana Department of Veterans Affairs to submit an annual report to the
3 Legislature of Louisiana detailing the length of time between a veteran's discharge
4 from military service and the filing of a claim for services.
5 WHEREAS, the Legislature of Louisiana recognizes the importance of ensuring that
6 all veterans of the United States Armed Forces receive timely access to the benefits, services,
7 and support to which they are entitled; and
8 WHEREAS, understanding the time interval between a veteran's discharge from
9 military service and the filing of a claim for services is essential to identifying barriers to
10 access, improving outreach, and strengthening the delivery of veterans' programs throughout
11 the state; and
12 WHEREAS, the Louisiana Department of Veterans Affairs (LDVA) is the state
13 agency charged with assisting veterans in securing federal and state benefits, providing
14 advocacy, and ensuring that veterans and their families receive appropriate support; and
15 WHEREAS, the legislature finds that regular reporting on claim-filing timelines will
16 assist policymakers in evaluating service gaps, improving program effectiveness, and
17 ensuring that Louisiana's veterans receive the highest standard of care; and
18 WHEREAS, it is both appropriate and necessary for the legislature to receive annual
