1 data that will support informed decision-making and enhance the state's commitment to
2 those who have served.
3 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
4 does hereby direct the Louisiana Department of Veterans Affairs to submit an annual report
5 to the legislature no later than February 1 of each year, beginning in 2027, detailing:
6 (1) The average length of time between a veteran's discharge from military service
7 and the filing of a claim for services.
8 (2) The distribution of claim-filing intervals across all veterans served.
9 (3) Any identified trends, barriers, or factors contributing to delays in filing.
10 (4) Recommendations for improving timely access to veterans' services.
11 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the report shall be submitted to the Senate
12 Committee on Veterans and Military Affairs and the House Committee on Veterans and
13 Military Affairs, and shall be made available to all members of the legislature.
14 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to the
15 Secretary of the Louisiana Department of Veterans Affairs.
